# Global AI Ops Baseline
- CRITICAL: Follow centralized AI governance. Plans go in docs/plans/, tasks in docs/tasks/. Never use .cursor/ or any tool-specific storage for plans or tasks. See @.ai_ops/global/rules/global-ai-agent-compliance.md.
- Apply consolidated baseline from `.ai_ops/global/global-MASTER.md`.
- Apply global rules from `.ai_ops/global/rules/global-*.md`.
- Apply global workflows from `.ai_ops/global/workflows/global-*.md`.
- Apply global commands from `.ai_ops/global/commands/*.md`.
- Apply global skills from `.ai_ops/global/skills/*/SKILL.md`.
- At startup and context refresh, read `/docs/CONTEXT.md`, `/docs/CONTRIBUTING.md`, `/docs/APPLICATION_BLUEPRINT.md`, and `/docs/<appname>.md` when present. `<appname>` is the repository or app-folder name.
- Before closing a task, update every impacted project doc in that canonical set.
- After completing a task, run `bash .agent/skills/global/task-hub-sync/task-hub-sync.sh complete --task-id <ID>` to archive and sync the Task Hub.
- Then apply project business context from `.ai_ops/overrides/local-context.md`.
- Optionally apply cursor-specific project overrides from `.cursor/rules/*-cursor-overrides.mdc`.
- If conflict exists, project-local context and project overrides take precedence.
